BEST croissants, delicious quiches, gelato, macaroons and more. You can order fresh bread prior to pick up. They serve (& sell beans) LaColombe coffee. Everyone is lovely. I catered a party from them and everything was perfect and reasonably priced. BTW they also accept cards.

My wife and I thought the chouquettes were delightful. Nice airy and lightly sweeten. Almost like France. The apple turnovers had a good filo dough to make it crusty (and a little messy). The French apple tart was similarly good. Everything was very well balanced in taste. Not overly sweet like Mediterranean pastries which tend to be drowned in honey. Less is sometimes more. Good job! Will be back.

Beny's Delice is a restaurant that has a huge variety of food. I've tried the ham and swiss egg tart, strawberry tart, blue berry tart, and the duck burger.  I will give 5 stars. Here are my reasons below:  1. The strawberry and blueberry tarts were fairly decent. They use natural fruits, which is great, and the design is well done.  2. The ham and swiss was very delicious and savory. It would be great for a quick breakfast, for it's very filling.  3. The duck burger was a surprise to me. The price for this particular item was 15 dollars. It comes with a salad, fries, and the burger. The price can be justified, if you look at it as 5 dollars per item. Usually salads are expensive  at many different establishments. I don't know if getting the burger alone would lower the price. However, it's still a good deal for a meal. The taste of the duck burger was very unique.  I don't recommend eating it hot, for you can not taste the flavor of the meat. 4. The cashier was very polite and patience. She also had a mask and gloves on during covid.

I am giving this establishment  3’stars Not because of the food, which is quite good, but because of something that happened this  morning. An elderly back woman walked into the cafe ahead of me, another black woman.  We spoke briefly and placed our orders. The counter staff thought we were together and charged both orders on the older woman’s card. The older woman was upset and accused the counter woman of racism. The counter woman who I will call Ms V said “ I am not racist.  I was born in New York.”  Give me a break! some of these so called liberal New Yorkers confuse charity and condescension for wokeness. Stiop making assumptions about people. I talk to everybody. It does not mean we are together. I wonder if Ms V would have made the same assumption had I been white  This may seem like a tempest in a teapot but this is how the evil starts. Your Assumptions may  lead to beliefs which in turn may lead to you treating the object of your assumptions differently.  Your staff need to better trained.

Beny's Delice you disappointed me. Very bad service and high price. Me and my husband used to go there every morning for croissants a coffee since we moved in the neighborhood two years ago. They had the best croissants in the neighborhood with a reasonable price. Then they raised their price which is understandable with the new buildings coming up. Then they raised again. We just see their price jumped from $2.25 to $3 to $3 plus tax. On top of that, the customer service has gone worse and worse. The current associates are really rude. I even feel bad ordering there as a customer; as they intimidate me, as if I did something wrong. I miss the old Beny's Delice and their lovely crew.

Most disappointing experience of a weekend in NYC. Went here for macarons after getting burritos down the street on a Friday afternoon. Got one pistachio macaron and one nutella. Ate the nutella first. I could not taste chocolate or hazelnut. I COULD taste the staleness of being refrigerated too long. An hour later I took a bite of the pistachio one. Same story. Could not taste pistachio but could taste staleness. Filling tasted like vanilla frosting from a can. Threw it away. I also bought a chocolate croissant but I was afraid to taste it after the macaron experience. My 5yo son enjoyed it.
